&lt;h2 id=&#34;div-style-text-align-left-evaluating-voice-conversion-based-privacy-protection-against-informed-attackers-div&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left;&#34;&gt; Evaluating Voice Conversion based Privacy Protection against Informed Attackers &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h6 id=&#34;div-style-text-align-left-brij-mohan-lal-srivastava-nathalie-vauquier-md-sahidullah-aurélien-bellet-marc-tommasi-and-emmanuel-vincent-div&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left;&#34;&gt; Brij Mohan Lal Srivastava, Nathalie Vauquier, Md Sahidullah, Aurélien Bellet, Marc Tommasi and Emmanuel Vincent &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/icassp.png&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 200px; background: #000000&#34; /&gt; 
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;outline&#34;&gt;Outline&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Context : need for privacy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Contributions
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Threat model
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Voice conversion based anonymization
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Experiments
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Results
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Conclusion
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;context&#34;&gt;Context&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Distinguishable&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Repeatable&lt;/em&gt; biometric references can be extracted from speech, such as, x-vectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advances in Speech synthesis, Voice cloning [1] and Speaker recognition pose severe privacy threat.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;attacker&lt;/strong&gt; tries to reveal the identity of the speaker in a public dataset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The attacker has access to some &amp;ldquo;found data&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;knowledge&amp;rdquo; of anonymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;contributions&#34;&gt;Contributions&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Compare anonymization using 3 voice conversion methods.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Design 3 attackers based on their &amp;ldquo;knowledge&amp;rdquo; of anonymization:

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ignorant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Semi-Informed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Evaluation of &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;privacy&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;utility&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;threat-model&#34;&gt;Threat model&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;width: 10em; height: 10em&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/threat_model_ppt1_1.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/threat_model_ppt2_2.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/threat_model_ppt3_3.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/threat_model_ppt_full.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&#34;voice-conversion-based-anonymization&#34;&gt;Voice conversion based anonymization&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;relevance&#34;&gt;Relevance&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logical speaker anonymization framework

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Convert &lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;source&lt;/span&gt; speaker&amp;rsquo;s voice to a &lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;target&lt;/span&gt; speaker
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Choice of &lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;target&lt;/span&gt; speaker is critical for strength of anonymization
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Allows data publication
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
First proposed in 2009 [2], many techniques proposed thereafter.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;three-vc-methods&#34;&gt;Three VC methods&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;VC methods are selected based on the following criteria:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Non-parallel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Many-to-many&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source/language independent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;three-vc-methods-1&#34;&gt;Three VC methods&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;VoiceMask&lt;/span&gt;: simple frequency warping based on composition of two functions $B$ and $Q$: $ f&amp;rsquo; = B(Q(f, \alpha), \beta) $
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;Vocal Tract Length Normalization&lt;/span&gt;: learn transformation parameters between source and target class spectra.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;Disentangled Speech Representation&lt;/span&gt;: Separate encoders for &lt;strong&gt;content&lt;/strong&gt; (instance normalization) and &lt;strong&gt;speaker&lt;/strong&gt; (average pooling) information.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&#34;experiments&#34;&gt;Experiments&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;target-selection-strategies&#34;&gt;Target selection strategies&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;width: 40em; height: 10em; margin-left: -8em&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/sconst.png&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 10em&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/sperm.png&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 10em&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/srand.png&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 10em&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;anonymization-framework&#34;&gt;Anonymization framework&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/anon_scheme.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 30em&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;design-of-attackers&#34;&gt;Design of Attackers&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;ignorant-attacker&#34;&gt;Ignorant attacker&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/ignorant_attacker.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 30em&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;semi-informed-attacker&#34;&gt;Semi-Informed attacker&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/semi_informed_attacker.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 30em&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;informed-attacker&#34;&gt;Informed attacker&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/informed_attacker.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 30em&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;training-data&#34;&gt;Training data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All the data subsets are derived from LibriSpeech corpus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table style=&#34;font-size: 30pt&#34;&gt;
    &lt;thead&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;th&gt;Component&lt;/th&gt;
            &lt;th&gt;Training data&lt;/th&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/thead&gt;
    &lt;tbody&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;VoiceMask&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;None&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;Disentangled VC&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;LibriTTS 100h&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;VTLN&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td rowspan=3&gt;LibriSpeech 460h&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;Attackers&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;ASR for evaluation&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;evaluation-data&#34;&gt;Evaluation data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;Male&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Female&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;

&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;#Speakers&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;13&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;16&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Genuine trials&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;449&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;548&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Impostor trials&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;9457&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;11,196&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;evaluation-protocol&#34;&gt;Evaluation protocol&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attackers are simulated using speaker verification, which produce PLDA scores.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;PLDA scores&lt;/span&gt; = log-likelihood ratio between &lt;em&gt;same-speaker&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;different-speaker&lt;/em&gt; hypotheses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Equal Error Rate (&lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;EER&lt;/span&gt;) is computed using PLDA scores.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Higher EER indicates &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;high privacy&lt;/span&gt;; Lower EER indicates &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;low privacy&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utility of anonymized speech is quantified using Word Error Rate (&lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;WER&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;results-on-privacy-eer&#34;&gt;Results on privacy (EER)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;font-size: 20pt&#34;&gt;As the knowledge of attacker increases, &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;privacy&lt;/span&gt; (EER) decreases.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;width: 10em; height: 10em&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_baseline.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_ig.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_si.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_in.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;plda-score-distribution&#34;&gt;PLDA score distribution&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More overlap between the score distribution ensures more privacy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overlap decreases as we move from &lt;em&gt;Ignorant&lt;/em&gt; to &lt;em&gt;Informed&lt;/em&gt; attacker.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/score_dist.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 40em&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;results-on-utility-wer&#34;&gt;Results on utility (WER)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;font-size: 20pt&#34;&gt;
- With rise in WER, utility decreases for all VC algorithms. &lt;br /&gt;
- VoiceMask and VTLN produce reasonable loss of utility.
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/wer_bars.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none;&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;conclusion&#34;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigated VC algorithms for speaker anonymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We show that &lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;target selection&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;attacker&amp;rsquo;s knowledge&lt;/span&gt; are critical for strength of anonymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simple methods can provide reasonable protection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;future-directions&#34;&gt;Future directions&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search for speaker anonymization which produces &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;high EER&lt;/span&gt;, even in &lt;em&gt;Informed&lt;/em&gt; attack scenario.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore cross-gender anonnymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse the PLDA scores using other metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;references&#34;&gt;References&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can we steal your vocal identity from the internet?: Initial investigation of cloning Obama’s voice using GAN, WaveNet and low-quality found data,” in Proc. Odyssey 2018&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jin et al, &amp;ldquo;Speaker de-identification via voice transformation&amp;rdquo;, ASRU 2009&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;questions&#34;&gt;Questions?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please email me at: &lt;code&gt;brij.srivastava@inria.fr&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/namaste.jpeg&#34; style=&#34;border: none;&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
